  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NE Humanitarian expert/ DG ECHO</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">NE Humanit&#xE4;rt samarbete/ DG ECHO</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Insatsen avser en sekundering av en nationell expert till DG ECHO och enheten B1 som ansvarar f&#xF6;r policyutveckling samt ramverk f&#xF6;r genomf&#xF6;rande g&#xE4;llande humanit&#xE4;rt bist&#xE5;nd/katastrofst&#xF6;d&#xE5;tg&#xE4;rder. Detta omfattar s&#xE5;v&#xE4;l sektorspecifik policy som horisontella aspekter - s&#xE4;rskilt relaterat till utdragna flykting- och migrationssitutaioner. 

Uppdraget syftar till att st&#xE4;rka DG ECHOs kapacitet att analysera, bed&#xF6;ma och kommuniciera  fr&#xE5;gor g&#xE4;llande internationell humanit&#xE4;r r&#xE4;tt (IHL), j&#xE4;mst&#xE4;lldhet, konfliktk&#xE4;nslighet, socialt skydd som ber&#xF6;r s&#xE4;kerst&#xE4;llandet av r&#xE4;ttigheter f&#xF6;r flyktingar och migranter i utdragna krissituationer. 

Enheten ansvarar f&#xF6;r att policys genomsyrar DG ECHOs verksamhet samt bedriver kommunikations- och p&#xE5;verkansarbete f&#xF6;r genomslag f&#xF6;r policy inom EU-institutionerna och genom relationen med relevanta internationella organisationer. Enheten ansvarar d&#xE4;rut&#xF6;ver f&#xF6;r framtagande av regionala strategier inom ramen f&#xF6;r direktoratets geografiska fokus: Europa, EU:s &#xF6;stra grannskap samt Mellan&#xF6;stern.

Sammanlagt inkom tv&#xE5; ans&#xF6;kningar, varav b&#xE4;gge bed&#xF6;mdes uppfylla meritkraven i arbetsbeskrivningen. DG ECHO genomf&#xF6;rde slutintervjuer med kandidaterna och valde  slutkandidat f&#xF6;r tj&#xE4;nsten i enlighet med meritkraven i arbetsbeskrivningen.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The contribution refers to a secondment of a national expert to DG ECHO and Unit B1 responsible for policy development and implementation framework for humanitarian aid /disaster relief measures. This includes both sector-specific policy and horizontal aspects - especially related to protracted refugee and migration situations.
The secondment aims to strengthen DG ECHO&apos;s capacity to analyze, assess and communicate issues relating to international humanitarian law (IHL), gender equality, conflict sensitivity, social protection related to the safeguarding of refugee and migrant rights in extended crisis situations.

The unit B1  is responsible for ensuring that policy is permeating DG ECHO&apos;s operations and to conduct communication to provide for policy coherence within the EU institutions and through its relations with relevant international organizations. In addition, the unit is responsible for developing regional strategies within the framework of the Directorate&apos;s geographical focus: Europe, the Eastern European Union and the Middle East.

A total of two applications were received, both of which were considered to meet the merit requirements in the job description. DG ECHO conducted final interviews with the candidates and selected the person considered most suited for the service in accordance with the job description.</narrative>
  </description>
